Projects

Project (1)
Selectivity of biorational insecticides and fungicides towards predators and entomopathogen fungus of vegetal pests in a tritrophic context
Project
The impact of pesticides on non-target organisms have reduced the biodiversity of agroecosystems and put in risk the ecosystem services given for natural enemies for the pest control. The objetives of this project are: 1) -To find selective biorational insecticides for the joint use with natural enemies in the framework of IPM, using Coccinellidae and Chrysopidae as diagnostic organisms; 2)-Evaluate the toxicity (lethal and sublethal) of fungicides commonly use in vegetal crops on predators and entomopathogen fungus, to categorize these compounds and determinate the ecotoxicological risks to natural enemies of pests.
